race.comment: NINE QUESTIONS (7) turned in a modest performance when fifth last time out over 1710m at this track, beaten 4 lengths. That followed a win at this track at the previous outing. Beautifully placed and is sure to make amends. MR CORN (10) improved last time out, finishing 0.8 lengths from the winner in second at the end of 1609m at this track. Finds an easier assignment and can get the job done. TEXAS CYCLONE (3) showed good early speed from the inside draw last start before finishing second over 1609m at this track (Turf). Meeting a tougher field but on his best form he is one of the key runners. ALPHA OMEGA (2) has recently experienced mixed fortunes. Failed to compelte the course at Kentucky last start. That followed an impressive win over 1609m at Ellis Park the run before.
